cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.AR, cs.CR, cs.DC 

The paper deals with modeling relaxed memory in computer systems, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the DRF theorem, which is related to concurrency theory (cs.AR) and correctness of algorithms (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper proposes a game-like model for well-justification, which could be considered a form of distributed computing (cs.DC).
